Reaching for that extra bit of yield can be a big mistake -- especially if you do n't understand what you 're investing in .
Just ask <COREF ID="25" TYPE="IDENT">Richard Blumenfeld , a New Jersey dentist who considers himself `` a reasonably sophisticated investor</COREF> . ''
