`` <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">It</COREF> was a time when interest rates came down very rapidly , '' <COREF ID="25" TYPE="IDENT">Dr. Blumenfeld</COREF> recalls .
Yields on five - year CDs at major banks were averaging about 7.45 % , and 10 - year <COREF ID="5" TYPE="IDENT">Treasury</COREF> notes were paying less than 8 % .
<COREF ID="3" TYPE="IDENT">The CD</COREF> seemed like a great deal .
